import React from 'react';
import {Link, NavLink} from 'react-router-dom';
import {Button, Nav, Navbar, NavDropdown, Form, FormControl} from 'react-bootstrap';
import './navbar.css';

const CustomNavbar = () => {
return(
// On small it collapses 

<Navbar className="bg-custom" expand="sm" variant="dark">
    <Form inline>
      <FormControl type="search" placeholder="Enter Keyword .." className="mr-sm-4" />
    </Form>
  <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="basic-navbar-nav" />
  <Navbar.Collapse id="basic-navbar-nav">
    <Nav className="mr-auto">
      <Nav.Link href="#home" >Home</Nav.Link>
      <Nav.Link href="#1" >World</Nav.Link>
      <Nav.Link href="#2" >Politics</Nav.Link>
      <Nav.Link href="#3" >Business</Nav.Link>
      <Nav.Link href="#4" >Technology</Nav.Link>
      <Nav.Link href="#5" >Sports</Nav.Link>
    </Nav>
    <Nav>
    <Form inline>
        <Navbar.Text className="mr-sm-4"> NY Times </Navbar.Text>
        <Form.Check type="switch" id="custom-switch" label="Guardian"/>
    </Form>
    </Nav>
  </Navbar.Collapse>
</Navbar>
)}

export default CustomNavbar
